<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-003-129 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 565 166</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 3 1991 v5 n41 p22(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Minding the net with Neon analyzer. (Neon Software Inc.'sNetMinder 2.0) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Neon Software Inc's $595 NetMinder 2.0 is an Ethernet networkprotocol analyzer that provides capture and analysis andexecutable configuration files.andP;  The program also includes two newutilities, one which lets users blindly capture packets and theother which surveys network and associate device Chooser nameswith their network addresses.andP;  The software-only analyzer ispriced much lower than DOS-based analyzers and offers onlinecontext-sensitive help for protocols and packets.andP;  The new versionalso can decode AppleTalk Update-based Routing Protocol (AURP),Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) and new TransmissionControl Protocol/Internet Protocol (TCP/IP) protocols.andP;  Theproduct works with Ethernet cards from such companies as SonicSystems Corp, Dayna Communications Inc and Technology Works Inc.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Neon Software Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   NetMinder Ethernet 2.0 (Network analyzer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNetwork AnalysisSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Margie WylieandM;Lafayette, Calif.andP;  -- A new Ethernet network troubleshooting tool nowshipping from Neon Software Inc. could save network managers from &quot;thinkingin hexidecimal,&quot; according to one beta tester.andM;Available now, the $595 NetMinder 2.0 is a software-only network protocolanalyzer that offers scriptlike, executable configuration files, on-the-flycapture and analysis, and two new utilities.andM;Something akin to an X-ray machine for networks, packet analyzers helpmanagers discover what ails their systems by capturing and decoding devicecommunications.andM;Joe Dallatore, senior network consultant for Marlton, N.J.-based systemsintegrator Computer Consulting Corp. and beta tester for NetMinder 2.0, usesthe software to troubleshoot a Wall Street investment bank's network.andM;&quot;I've found [Version 2.0] very easy to give to users who aren't Snifferheads,&quot; he said, referring to a DOS-based packet analyzer from NetWorkGeneral Corp.andM;Dallatore uses Version 2.0's configuration files to help users helpthemselves.andM;&quot;I leave the application and the configuration file on a Mac, and all usershave to do is click on the document the next time they experience [apersistent] problem,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;I look at the file any time I want.&quot;andO;Configuration files consist of a script of triggers, filters and reports thatare set in motion when the file is opened.andM;NetMinder 2.0 can capture and analyze packets on the fly, as opposed to theprevious version, which required users to complete capturing packets beforethey began decoding them.andP;  The network neophyte can get help sleuthing outsnafus with on-line context-sensitive help for packets and protocols.andM;The program ships with two new utilities: One automatically surveys a networkand associates devices' Chooser names with their network addresses, a manualfunction in the past; a second lets users blindly capture but not analyzepackets.andM;Like other software-only analyzers, such as The AG Group's EtherPeek,NetMinder costs only a fraction of what DOS-based analyzers go for.andP;  &quot;Itgives me 90 percent of the functionality of a Sniffer at 5 percent of theprice,&quot; Dallatore said.andM;Version 2.0 also decodes SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol); AppleTalkUpdate-based Routing Protocol (AURP) -- a new standard protocol for AppleTalkconnections over wide-area links; and new TCP/IP protocols, including thoseused by Banyan Corp.'s VINES.andM;NetMinder 2.0 works with several new Ethernet cards from makers DaynaCommunications Inc., Technology Works Inc., Sonic Systems Corp. and Tri-DataSystems Inc.andM;Those who buy NetMinder Ethernet after Oct.andP;  9 get a free upgrade; others pay$75.andM;Neon Software Inc. is at 1009 Oak Hill Road, Suite 203, Lafayette, Calif.andO;94549.andP;  Phone (415) 283-9771; fax (415) 283-6507.andO;</TEXT></DOC>